race.description: Moretti Constructions Kembla Grange Cup Handicap
race.comment: CAN'T TOUCH THIS (11) returned to form last start with an all-the-way win over this distance at Nowra. Can be a little hard to catch but is a very handy mare when on-song. Well drawn and should be prominent for a long way. COPACABANA (3) is back from nearly a year on the sidelines. Placed three from three when fresh and a couple of strong recent trials suggest things are on track. AUTUMN BLONDE (6) just faded in the closing stages at Newcastle last start. Very fit filly who will enjoy the run of the race from the inside alley. In the mix in this suitable race. PANIC (1) returns from a 29-week lay-off. The winner of two from four when fresh. Good recent trial form suggests he is ready to make an immediate impact. SMASHING TIME (2) is a strong fresh performer who has not appeared since 5 July. Recent trial winner here and looks set for a bright return.
